Author: ErikB#3019
Content:
I recently had a discussion with a Venezuelan woman who is married to a multimillionaire.

I asked her, “What are people doing to buy food down there in Venezuela? Do people use Bitcoin?” 

She then responded saying, “No, not really. The government made it illegal to use cryptocurrency... But I have some family that tried to sell their house with Fake Bitcoin, and so I asked my husband to look into it, and he saved them from selling the house in return for Fake Bitcoin.”

I said, “Wow that’s crazy.” And took a nice little mental note lol

My feeling afterward was that legacy playaz (“Playaz” being the $100m+ crowd) are very aware of the space, and likely more aware than we think 🤙
